Not quite â€” you can't paste this entire Node.js + Puppeteer code into a Cloudflare Worker, because:

âš ï¸ Why It Wonâ€™t Work in Workers
âŒ Cloudflare Workers Limitations:
Feature	Cloudflare Workers
Node.js modules (e.g. express, puppeteer)	âŒ Not supported
Headless browser (puppeteer)	âŒ Not allowed
fs, child_process, net, etc.	âŒ Blocked
Long processes or file system	âŒ Not allowed
External fetch + JSON + proxy	âœ… Supported âœ…

âœ… What You Can Do in a Worker
Once your VPS API is live (like):

bash
Copy
Edit
http://your-vps-ip:3000/api/latest-m3u8
Then you can make a Cloudflare Worker like this:

js
Copy
Edit
export default {
  async fetch(request, env, ctx) {
    const res = await fetch("http://your-vps-ip:3000/api/latest-m3u8");

    if (!res.ok) {
      return new Response("Failed to fetch stream", { status: 500 });
    }

    const data = await res.json();

    const m3u8Response = await fetch(data.m3u8, {
      headers: {
        "Referer": "https://app.blasttv.ph"
      }
    });

    const text = await m3u8Response.text();

    return new Response(text, {
      headers: { "Content-Type": "application/vnd.apple.mpegurl" }
    });
  }
}
